		"description": "<p><em>Breaker (Wood), Heavy, Two-Handed</em></p>\n<p>This greataxe is macabre in design, bearing a black axehead that seems to shimmer in darkness and a solid white handle that feels like ironhard bone that&rsquo;s always cool to the touch. You gain a +1 bonus on attack and damage rolls using this greataxe.</p>\n<p>Once you have attuned to black axe, it gains the following properties.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Black Blight.</strong></em> Necrotic damage dealt by this greataxe ignores damage resistance . A target immune to necrotic damage takes half damage from necrotic damage dealt by black axe.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Dark Hunger.</strong></em> While you are bloodied and wielding this greataxe, you can use a bonus action to make a melee attack against a living creature within your reach. On a hit, you deal an extra 2d8 necrotic damage, gaining temporary hit points equal to the necrotic damage dealt.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Flesheater.</strong></em> You can use an action to touch black axe against the corpse of a Medium-sized or smaller creature. The greataxe consumes all of the corpse&rsquo;s blood, bones, and flesh to leave only the items it was wearing. Once you have used this property a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, you must finish a long rest before it can be used again.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Curse: Bloodlust.</strong></em> You are unwilling to part with the greataxe, and you have disadvantage on attacks made against non-bloodied creatures when a living enemy within 30 feet of you is bloodied.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
